cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.PL

The paper deals with a formal system for number theory based on computability logic, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses complexity constraints on algorithmic solutions, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of parameters to obtain sound and complete theories is also related to information theory (cs.IT) and programming languages (cs.PL).
